{"id": "27795", "post": "<div class=\"post-27795 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-editorial tag-crime tag-cybercriminal tag-hosting-industry tag-insurance tag-ransomware tag-security\" id=\"post-27795\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/insurers-tire-of-paying-ransom-to-cyber-crooks/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Insurers Tire of Paying Ransom to Cyber Crooks</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/crime/\" rel=\"tag\">crime</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/cybercriminal/\" rel=\"tag\">cybercriminal</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/hosting-industry/\" rel=\"tag\">hosting industry</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/insurance/\" rel=\"tag\">insurance</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/ransomware/\" rel=\"tag\">ransomware</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/security/\" rel=\"tag\">Security</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> July 20, 2021 @ 12:00 am, by raindog308</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/empty_wallet.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-27796 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/empty_wallet.jpg\" alt=\"empty wallet\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" align=\"right\" hspace=\"20\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/empty_wallet.jpg 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/empty_wallet-150x150.jpg 150w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/empty_wallet.jpg 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/empty_wallet-150x150.jpg 150w\" data-was-processed=\"true\">Loss ratios in the cyber insurance world have skyrocketed in recent years \u2013 surging 400% year over year.&nbsp; They have hit <a href=\"https://www.fitchratings.com/research/insurance/sharply-rising-cyber-insurance-claims-signal-further-risk-challenges-15-04-2021\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"fitchratings.com\">70% of paid premiums</a>, which some industry commentators are saying is unsustainable.</p><p>Previously, standard policy was to \u201cpay the ransom,\u201d but this attitude may be changing.&nbsp;\u201cThe ransomware groups got way too greedy too quickly. So the cost-benefit equation the insurers initially used to figure out whether or not they should pay a ransom \u2014 it\u2019s just not there anymore,\u201d <a href=\"https://apnews.com/article/kaseya-ransomware-attack-0705-4c2272cdd428ddfa1f3644d513566c06\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"apnews.com\">said Fabian Wosar</a>, CTO of Emsisoft, a cybersecurity firm that specializes in ransomware.</p><p>Determining how much insurance companies have is standard operating procedure for would be data kidnappers \u2013 either by obtaining the information as part of their attack or comparing the company size to payouts made by others.&nbsp; More <a href=\"https://therecord.media/i-scrounged-through-the-trash-heaps-now-im-a-millionaire-an-interview-with-revils-unknown/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"REvil Article\">sophisticated criminals</a> have penetrated insurers to determine how much coverage clients have before attacking those clients.</p><p>However, some insurers are now no longer reimbursing ransoms.&nbsp; Insurer <a href=\"https://apnews.com/article/europe-france-technology-business-caabb132033ef2aaee9f58902f3e8fba\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"AP News\">AXA announced</a> that it will no longer reimburse for ransoms.&nbsp; Global total ransom in 2020 was <a href=\"https://blog.emsisoft.com/en/38426/the-cost-of-ransomware-in-2021-a-country-by-country-analysis/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"Ransomware Article\">hat least $18 billion</a>.</p><p>Insurance costs have mounted in recent years, rising nearly 40% year-over-year.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/how-tostiff-arm-brutes-and-protect-your-server-with-fail2ban/\"><div class=\"relpost-custom-block-single\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=\"fail2ban\" style=\"background: transparent url(https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/fail2ban-150x150.png) no-repeat scroll 0% 0%; width: 150px; height: 150px;\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-single-text\" style=\"font-family: Arial;  font-size: 12px;  color: #333333;\">How to Stiff-Arm Brutes and Protect Your Server with Fail2Ban</div></div></a><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/beware-black-hat-cookie-stuffing-affiliate-marketing/\"><div class=\"relpost-custom-block-single\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=\"Cookie Monster\" style=\"background: transparent url(https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/cookie_monster-150x150.png) no-repeat scroll 0% 0%; width: 150px; height: 150px;\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-single-text\" style=\"font-family: Arial;  font-size: 12px;  color: #333333;\">Beware Black Hat Cookie Stuffing Affiliate Marketing</div></div></a><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/seven-years-in-the-making-interv